\[f(f(f(x))) = f(x).\]Let $a = f(x),$ so
\[a = f(f(a)).\]Let $b = f(a),$ so $a = f(b).$  Thus, both $(a,b)$ and $(b,a)$ lie on the graph of $y = f(x).$  In other words, $(a,b)$ lie on the graph of $y = f(x)$ and $x = f(y).$

